<P>Judgement</P>
</CHAR_OUTCOMES>
<CHAR_NOTES>
<P>Power calculation: N/A</P>
<P>In the assessment of siblings' fear of catching their brother's or sister's cancer, the study found 3/4 scores to be statistically signifcant. The paired t-test p values for the change in scores before and after are: 0.38, 0.01, 0.08 and 0.08. The authors' interpretation of these results is questionable, as only the 0.01 p value appears to indicate a statistically significant change.</P>
